				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {F}_{\mathrm{EK}}=\frac{\sigma_d{E}_{\parallel }}{\delta_0} $$\end{document}where σd is the charge density of the diffuse layer, EII is the induced nonelectrostatic field, and δ0 is the boundary layer thickness [9, 10]. The electrokinetic force causes, like in the case of Lorentz force, the induction of convection in the solution [11].

